snippet.title: the travelling surrogate
snippet.description:
I am happily childfree but I have always had a curiosity about pregnancy. I decided to follow in my Mum's footsteps by becoming a traditional surrogate; which means I got pregnant by means of artificial insemination to create a family for a wonderful couple. Extreme babysitting for 9 months, followed by 12 months  maternity leave travelling the world 🌍

Altruistic surrogacy is legal in the UK meaning I was only reimbursed pregnancy expenses.
